# PARKING LOT SYSTEM - Requirement Clarification & Discussion
## Amazon SDE2 LLD Interview Prep

---

## 🎯 Problem Statement
Design a **Parking Lot System** that can handle multiple vehicle types, assign appropriate parking spots, track entry/exit times, and calculate fees based on duration.

---

## 🗣️ Clarifying Questions & Answers

### 1. WHO — Actors

| Actor | Role |
|-------|------|
| **Driver** | Parks vehicle, pays fee |
| **Entry Gate** | Issues ticket, assigns spot |
| **Exit Gate** | Collects ticket, calculates fee, processes payment |
| **Admin** | Configures floors, spots, pricing (out of scope) |

---

### 2. WHAT — Vehicles & Spots

**Q: What types of vehicles?**

| Vehicle Type | Spot Size Needed | Hourly Rate |
|--------------|------------------|-------------|
| Motorcycle | Small | ₹20/hr |
| Car | Medium | ₹40/hr |
| Truck/Bus | Large | ₹60/hr |

**Q: What sizes of spots?**

| Spot Size | Can Park |
|-----------|----------|
| Small | Motorcycle only |
| Medium | Motorcycle, Car |
| Large | Motorcycle, Car, Truck |

**Rule:** A vehicle can park in a spot of **its size or larger**.

